The global injectable drug delivery market is segmented based on different factors to provide a comprehensive understanding of the industry landscape. The market is categorized by type into conventional drug delivery and novel drug delivery. Conventional drug delivery methods have been widely used but are now being phased out in favor of more advanced novel drug delivery systems that offer improved precision and efficacy. In terms of application, the market is segmented into autoimmune diseases, hormonal disorders, and oncology. Injectable drug delivery plays a crucial role in treating these conditions effectively. Furthermore, the distribution channel segment includes hospitals, clinics, and ambulatory surgical centers as key points of access for patients to receive injectable medications.

